Swamp Rabbits Off-Road Cycling
description:
Start Smart Events presents Swamp Rabbits Off Road Cycling Club and Camp, Fall of 2016. Beginning the first weekend of September and ending the first weekend of October at the GetOut! Greenville Family Festival,. The program activities will consist of skills development of off road bike handling and explanation of technique in all related activities. 

Event and Clinic location w/ date:
•	Greenville CX-Cup #1 September 10th- Trailblazer Park 
•	Carolina Cyclocross Omnium Oct 1-2 - Conestee Park Day 1 / TrailerBlazer Day 2 
•	Tryon Difficile Ultra Cross Oct 15th - Harmon Field ( NC ) 65 Mile Gravel Road Race
•	Swamp Rabbits Off Road Cycling Club - 5 Weeks Sept Wk 1-4 Oct Wk 1-2 
•	Hincapie Sportswear Jersey

Fall 2016 Start Smart Events calendar offers four competitive off road racing events and a five week youth off-road cycling camp.  Camp members will become part of the Swamp Rabbits Club, a one of-a-kind group, with a direct link to the racing and recreational community.  We are partnered in this venture by Greenville County Parks and Recreation of South Carolina.
course: Courses will change for each venue.
registration:
Register online at USA Cycling to join the club, or register for the camp.

title: Cycle Haus Carolina Cyclocross Omnium

address.street: Conestee Park & Trailblazer Park in Greenville, SC. County

description:
The Carolina Cyclocross Omnium presented by Cycle Haus Bicycle Shop.  The omnium races kickoff Saturday Oct 1st at Conestee Park in Greenville County.  The CX Time Trial beginning at 8:00 AM might be chilly.  We will have coffee onsite!  Our premier event,  the Carolina CX race starts with masters 40+ racers at 11:00 am.  
The race weaves through the Greenville County Family Festival, GetOut! Greenville throughout the day and promised huge crowds!  Many local food trucks and outdoor activities for families and friends during this all day event!

notes:
Save the date for the first CX race in Greenville SC, the Greenville CX-Cup!  Races begin at 10 AM - Full schedule of Youth, Amateur and Professional races.  Course will have two dismount sections, a challenging hill  (or two) and many long straightaway sections for riders to pick up some speed.  
Bring your friends and family to Trailblazer Park!  Enjoy the Travelers Rest Farmers Market and beautiful start to Fall weather in Travelers Rest South Carolina.
